  <metadata />
  <rte>
    <name>Ullock Pike, Long Side and Carl Side</name>
    <desc>Ullock Pike, Long Side and Carl Side are three Wainwrights connected by a high ridge that is located on the south-western aspect of Skiddaw. The views south over Lake Bassenthwaite, the north-western fells, Keswick and Derwentwater are good and provide ample reason for completing this straightforward out and back excursion along the ridge.</desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1676-description</url>
